\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 On sweets generally - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Did anyone outside the home help your mother to look after the house or family? Like relations of friends or neighbours?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 No relations nor no friends. We had a charwoman that - who used to come in twice a week. Tuesday for washing and Friday for cleaning.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 If
 your mother was ill or confined to bed how did she manage - do you remember what happened when the children were born - who helped her then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 I don't remember - I was the last one nearly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Did you have relatives living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Only the grandfather lived two doors from us - we lived then in Fenny Street. We lived at 60 and granddad lived at 66.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Did you see much of him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Oh yes. 'Cos he owned the houses. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Did your parents have a lot of friends and where did they see them - did they share the same friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 No, no, not a lot of friends. Only relations, yes, that's right. A brother at Sale who we used to go to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 So you never had friends invited to the home at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 No. Can't say - only family, like - in-laws and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Did they come regularly or did they just come on special occasions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Oh no, they called at - when they were anywhere near to or - just make a visit to see -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Just call in casually?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 People often s
ay that in those days they made their own amusements, how did your parents enjoy themselves when they were with relatives - did they make music or did they play games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 No, they didn't play games - they just did a lot of talking together. That's all I remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 
Many people in those days divided society into different social groups or classes, in that time before 1919 did you think of some belonging to one class and some to another and can you tell me what the difference was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Well, perhaps - bit conceited - I thought I was a little bit - a cut above the others.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Which class would you say you belonged to yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Better working class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 What sort of people belonged to the same class as yourself would you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Shopkeepers and - tailors.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 What about the other classes that you mentioned - say the lower working classes, what type of people do you think belonged to these?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Well, I should say - oh - I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Were you ever brought up to treat one sort of people di
fferent from another? Were you ever told to show respect in some way to certain people?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 
Oh yes, we were always made to show respect for people but there are some class of people you can't mix with you see, isn't there. Because - they somehow or anot
her didn't seem to be in the same region as you are - things that you'd say they'd think you were - putting a show on or something like that you know, trying to be superior to them. I remember one of my - school mates - school friends and we had been very
 good friends really and when I went to the finishing school and coming home one day and she said I was an upstart. Yes. Yes, she said, oh, she said, you're a snob. And I never forgave her for it because I wasn't a snob - I didn't think I was anyhow.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Was there anyone you called Sir or Madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 
Oh yes, I think so. I think the landlady that we had before we came to - to live in our own house - I always used to call her Madam, Miss or Madam, and she invariably had a way of holding a penny and a half-a-
crown in her hand and she'd say now which will you have. And mother'd say, now then, and I'd ask for the penny. And she'd say - you can have the half-crown, love, if you want. And I'd say, no thank you, I'll have the penny.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Do you ever remember anyone showing respect to your parents in this way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Not saying Sir or Madam - they'd say Mr so-and-so - Mr Holton - Mr - Mrs Holton that was all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 In the district where you lived who were considered the most important people in those days and did you c
ome in contact with them? And why did you think they were important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 
No, I can't say I do in that respect. There was a - the doctor and the magistrate - lived at the corner or Fenny Street and Bury New Road. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1380818\charrsid9666090 Mackeson}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090  I think his name was. Yes, that was close to us and then there was ....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Did you come into contact with them at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Not with Mr }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1380818\charrsid9666090 Mackeson}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090  we didn't. But of course we came in contact with the doctor and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Why do you think they were considered important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 I suppose becau
se they were professionals of - of kind of another. You know, educated people, more - elevated than the ordinary run of people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 What about shopkeepers - who do you think they mixed with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 I don't think they mixed with anybody any different than the neighbours round about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 What about the clergy? Do you think they mixed with a certain type of person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Yes, I remember the priest at the church, he used to associate with the police across the road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1380818\charrsid9666090 Well, from all accounts he w
as rather fond of his bottle and he used to go and have a game of cards and this bottle with him - from all accounts. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 
Yes. From this church here to the police - the old police station. And he'd have - oh no, I won't say that. He'd a - He'd a very broken ou
t nose and of course I suppose they all used to account for it with the bottle - it was whisky he was very fond of I believe.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 What about teachers - who do you think they mixed with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Oh, they mixed with one another I think, I don't think they bothered much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Did you know any farmers?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Farmers? No. Not when I was young I didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 What about employers - who do you think they would associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Employers? Oh, I suppose - I never met any - but I suppose they associated amongst themselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 What sort of people do you think went to church and which went to the chapel - did you notice any difference between them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Well, yes I did. The church people - they - they were more on a level with their interests and the - their religion whereas the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 In which way do you mean on a level?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 
Well, they seemed to - how can I explain that now - they - they didn't seem to prate so much about it or talk so much about it as - the - chapel people. The chapel people somehow they used 
to - be always having functions to sort of interest the - people around about you see. Whereas the church people, they were satisfied with the church and they didn't elaborate on it in any way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Have I got the idea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 You were Roman Catholic - did you find a lot of prejudice towards Roman Catholics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Oh definitely, yes, when we were young - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Was it very bad in this district - in Broughton?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Well, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Did you have a big Jewish community too or is it just recently its become a Jewish community?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 
Oh, it's been growing for twenty or thirty years now and of course they have got well on have the Jewish people now. But of course in the days gone by we - were a bit - against them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 And what about Roman Catholics - were they against Roman Catholics around here too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Oh - you mean the Jews?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Was there prejudice against the Roman Catholics around here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Oh, definitely - yes, but ....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 What way was it shown?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Well, latterly - since the new church had been b
uilt and all that kind of thing we've got a lot of - householders now that are Catholics you see, and they're more or less in the majority. But - they don't seem to have any bother with them now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 But they did when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Perhaps you n
oticed it more as a child. You'd hear them calling quack quacks and all that kind of things you know - amongst some children mostly. Yes. But - you see them now pouring out of the church - sort of strikes me as comical is the they go to church in the morn
ings -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 This is nowadays you're talking about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 
But where you lived did all the people in the working class have the same standard of living or do you think there were different standards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Oh yes, I - I think so. 'Course it all depe
nded upon the parents as to who - if you'd got a house or where they'd got a - a drunken dad or something like that, of course the youngsters went a bit short didn't they. And - they always seemed to be downtrodden somehow.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 And you think the difference was where the father drank?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 I think - where he drank or betted, that kind of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 You felt this was the big difference?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Yes. But - well, it caused more - poverty and degradation as you may call it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Do you think that one group felt itself superior to the rest? Were some families thought of as rough and others as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 
Oh definitely - there was always that attitude amongst neighbours and that. Some couldn't care less and other were trying to elevate themselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Do you think there was a big distinction of this kind between craftsmen and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 
Definitely. Oh yes, definitely. It was quite a thing - oh he's only a labourer, you see, or - he's a - he's a craftsman. You see, well, a craftsman was a craftsman be
cause he'd had to serve his time whereas a labourer just fell in and yes, did what he was told to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Did your mother and father have this same attitude to people in different groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Well, there was always that attitude of - seeking your own level.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Do you think your mother saw herself as belonging to a particular social group and do you know why this was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 No, no, I don't think so. She - she had that attitude that a parent was a parent and they were there to bring up the children in a 
proper manner. Keep a clean home and - and - well-kept garments and things like that. Of course, as far as that she would consider herself superior to a careless housewife you see and of course she always saw that instead of romping in the streets as you 
g
rew older you had plenty of knitting to do for the family - making undergarments - mending sheets - reversing sheets - pillowcases - that was my job. That was my job - to keep the bedding and everything in - in proper action and she would see that you did
 it too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 
Do you think it was possible in those days to move up say from working class to middle class - move up from one group to another? Do you know anyone that did it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Well, yes, I think so. There - they sort of gave up their old job and took up something else and they found that they improved themselves.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Did you know anyone who did this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Oh, you don't want me to mention names do you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Just tell me about the person and what they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Yes. There was a - a family who - he was
 an ordinary working man and took up - the newspaper business and he became and agent for newspapers you see so that he was a step ahead then you see, with that. And he moved up in his class naturally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Do you remember anyone being described as a real lady or a real gentleman and why do you think they were called this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 
Yes. They were several ladies round about and - you could always pick them out because they didn't wear - the - fashionable clothes that comes along. They weren't always dressed ali
ke, you know, like a lot of sheep all dolled up in the same - they always wore distinctive clothes - something away from the popular fashions as they call them today. And - well - yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Do you remember seeing a policeman round where you lived as a child and what did you think of him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 I don't know - I don't think I thought anything about them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Did your mother ever threaten you with a policeman - say I'll call a policeman if you're naughty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 No. No. She used to get the cat of nine tails and - it was - give us a smack.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Would you know how he treated the people in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 
Oh, I think with respect. Different than they do today. I don't remember seeing any policemen when I was a youngster - not to remember them. They didn't impress me I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 You did say that you lived in one home that was rented - did you see anything of your landlord? Did you say it was Bowker Street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Did you ever see the landlord and what did you think of him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Oh, he was a very nic
e chap - a Mr Gould - he was a very nice man. Suppose really he'd - worked hard and saved hard and bought this property and - he'd no edge about him or anything like that you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Do you rather like him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Yes, he came along and he was very civil and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Do you remember ever feeling that your parents had to struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 
Yes. I do. Yes. Yes, we had - we had to meet that when my parents came out of business. Yes, it was touch and go then. That was in Green Street when I was about - I'd be four or five. But I can always remember the difference in our form of living.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 It suddenly dropped did it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Yes, and - 'course it was only just for a we while - it didn't last long but it was there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 How did you feel about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 It was a set back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 How did you feel as a child - would you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 
No, I don't remember - my dad used to - buy me cakes and things - I didn't feel the - the tinge at all but I can remember that it was a change from - our business days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Was your father ever ill or out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Only when they gave up the business until he took on a - the insurance job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Did you ever have to go to anyone for help when your father was out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 No. No. Only that incident with the pea soup and I wasn't sent for it. That was getting into mischief.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 
Do you remember if anyone did anything wrong in the community that the people didn't like - how did they show their disapproval - there were lots of ways that they showed it - do you remember this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Yes, they wouldn't see them - they'd look }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1380818\charrsid9666090 through}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090  them or - and not see them kind of.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Have you ever heard of them making effigies of them or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 No. No, I can't say that I have - no, I can't say that I've - oh I'm afraid I wasn't educated up to that at that period - no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Were you ever given lessons at home by your parents or tutor or governess?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Not lessons but - help by my dad - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 But you went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Oh yes, always went to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 How old were you when you went to your first school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Oh, about four I think. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 What time in the morning did you start?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Nine o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 And did you go to afternoon school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Afternoon school too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 What time did you finish afternoon school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Half past four I think if I remember -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 So you worked from nine 'til half past four?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 What kind of a school was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 It's Catholic school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Church school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Yes. St }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1380818\charrsid9666090 Aloicious}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Was it boys and girls mixed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Oh yes. St Alouicious in Ardwick - I can remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 And it was boys and girls mixed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Mixed - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 How did you get to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 We used to walk. It was quite a distance.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 How long did it take you? Do you remember who went with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Oh about ten minutes I suppose - we'd run to school we wouldn't walk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Did you have anyone go with you at all? Did anyone take you to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 No, I think I went myself mostly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Where did you have your mid-day meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Come home for it - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 What did you think of school - did you like it or dislike it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Oh, I liked it - I've always liked school. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 How did you feel about the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 I liked them very much. I didn't - I can't remember the names of the teachers at St Alouic}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3352693\charrsid9666090 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 ous}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3352693\charrsid9666090 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 
s when I went but - I could at - later on mother took me from St. Alouic}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3352693\charrsid9666090 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 ous}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3352693\charrsid9666090 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 s and I went to Burley Street board school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 That would we totally different wouldn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 When you were at St }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3352693\charrsid9666090 Alouicious}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090  did they teach you certain things that were important in life like manners or tidiness, punctuality or ways of speaking - anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 No. No, we used to sit on a - a sort of a - gallery and what I can remember of it was mostly like threading piec
es of paper through it and out. And of course we had religious teaching and prayers - quite a few of those.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 They didn't teach that certain things were important though - you didn't remember this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 No, I think we were too young to take it in any case.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 What happened if you did anything wrong - did they punish you and how did they do it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 I mustn't have done anything wrong because I don't remember any punishment.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 You don't remember anyone else being punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 No. No, I think I must have been a good girl.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Did the children come from the same type of background as your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 I think they must have done, I - I wouldn't know - I was only four.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Do you remember the teachers singling out some children for different treatment to others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 No, not at that period I didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 There wouldn't be gangs or groups in this school would there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Were there any children left out of things do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 No, we all seemed to sit as quiet as nice on this gallery.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 You left there and you went to a board school - did you actually live in? Can you tell me about this school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Not a - they called them boarding schools - the board schools - council school it would be but they called them board schools - B
urley Street board school they called it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 How old were you when you went there then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 I'd be about - I must have been about five I think. Yes, about five I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Did you stay the full day or did you just do mornings or afternoons?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Wel
l, you see, they had two hours in the dinner time then didn't they. From twelve to two and you used to come home to dinner. But it was quite a walk from - from - Ardwick to - to Burley Street board school.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Did you walk it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Walk it - oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Did you go on your own still?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Yes, yes. Well, of course, it wasn't the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13982993\charrsid9666090 vagabonds}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090  around then as there are now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 You still came home to lunch did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Came home to dinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Do you remember anything particular about this school what the
 teachers emphasise in their training of you - what they considered important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 
Well, there were the three R's to start with. Yes. Reading writing and arithmetic. Yes. We got that. And we were taught to be obedient and the teachers name I remember alw
ays - Miss Belinda Thresher - yes, Miss Belinda Thresher. it's - its always stuck in my memory that did and she was very dark, curly hair - and she was very kind to us - very kind indeed. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Did she take you right through the school or did you have other teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 No, she - just in the one class. She was the teacher of our class, as we called it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 What did you think of the other teachers - did you like them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 I don't remember - I don't remember any of the others. Just this - Miss Belinda -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Was it a boys and girls school combined?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Yes, it was a mixed school - what I remember -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Do you remember being punished there or anybody being punished there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 No, I can't remember anybody had - I didn't go in for punishment.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 You never remember anyone else being punished and what it was for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 No, I don't - I don't ever remember anyone being punished.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Were these children from similar backgrounds at this school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Oh, I think they were all working class - peoples children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Did you have gangs in this school at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 No, we were - didn't understand gangs in those days. Just - we might have just one special - playmate or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Do you ever remember anyone left out of things there in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 No. No. I remember sometimes - we were put in a corner with a dunces cap on. I wasn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 That was a form of punishment then wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Yes. We - if they were slow at learning and that they'd take them out put them in a corner with the dunce}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13982993\charrsid9666090 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 s hat on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 That was rather cruel wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Well, I - I - the other children I don't think worried very much. Perhaps the child with the dunces hat on did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Did teachers single out some children for different treatment from others?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 N
o, I don't think so. This - this Miss Belinda Thresher - she seemed to be very equal to them all. I don't think she bothered - made any distinction.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Did your parent take an interest in your school work - did they ask what you did at school or visit th
e school or see the teachers or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 
No, I don't think they visited the school but they used to want to know what we were doing - our lessons. And of course dad would be interested in us. He used to want to know all about it and - and 
show us how to work these sums out if we were a bit stuck you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Did you have a part time job while you were at school to make pocket money or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 No, not - not with any spends - got plenty of - come out and mind the class and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Did you ever have a job at evenings or weekends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 What about your first full time job - what was it - do you remember? When you left school and you got your first full time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Oh, I didn't - I didn't get any job at all until three years after I was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3280094 Married}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 . I was at home always. Never went out - no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 You used to help your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 I was at home and - doing the housework.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Did you like it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 I didn't. But I - had to do as I was told.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Would you have preferred to have gone out to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Oh yes, I'd have liked to have gone out to work but - it - that was out of the question.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Then you took this job three years after you were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3280094 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Yes, after my -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Was this the one with the Mail you told me about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Oh no. My first job was at - at - Trafford Park as a - as a - as a clerk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 What year would that be - would you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 I think it would be about 1934. That's right. About 1934. I was a stock clerk - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Did you go on to the Mail from there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 No. I did a lot of - I was there for six months and then - I was on Russian Traffic. Then the Russians turned turtle and everything -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 What was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Wagons and things like that coming through - supplies, you see. And then
 - everything was at a standstill then. Goods had been received into the warehouse and there they stopped I suppose and then I was out of work for quite a while and then I got a job at the food office. But I was only there a fortnight because - I'd - prio
r to getting that job at the food office - I'd been all round Swinton and Pendlebury - seeing if I could find a job. And whilst I was at the food office - one of the firms had sent for me for a permanent job.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 This was in the '30's was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Yes. So -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 When you left school you stayed at home didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Oh, I had to stay at home to help my mother to do the housework - cooking and all what have you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Did you spend your Sundays any differently as you got older - did you still go to church on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Oh yes. Oh yes, yes, yes. Always went to churches - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Did you go out in the evenings more after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Yes, I was allowed two evenings a - one evening a week - Wednesday - one evening a week, Wednesday, and every 
other Sunday - afternoon or evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 How did you spend your free time then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Well, you'd go out with your friend and have a walk to Kersal Moor and - back again and - to and from you know how they did in those days.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 You didn't go to dances or ....?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 No, I wasn't allowed to go to dances.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Did you go to theatres or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 No, not - only with dad at Christmas time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Did you make a lot of new friends when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 No, not a lot. No, not a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Did you have any special friends, boys or girls? Did your parents meet them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 
I had a friend - and - I think I mentioned it before - where she came to see if I could come out and my mother said 'no, if your parents can't find you something to do I can f
ind my daughter something to do'. And she wouldn't let me out. That was when I - oh I was - nineteen or twenty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Did you never bring friends to your home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 If you went out your parents wanted to know where you were and ....?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Oh, they wanted to know all about it. Where you'd been.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 You had to be back at a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 What time was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Half past nine. Oh dear me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 What age were you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3280094 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 ?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Twenty-seven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 How long had you known your husband?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 About - about four years I think.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Where did you meet him - was it at church or at a dance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 No, it was at a friends house. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Where did he come from - was he a Salford boy too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Oh yes, he came - from - Newhall Farm, Pendleton. It was Browns the butchers place you know, his father was the ....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Browns the big butchers in Manchester?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Yes. They were - his father was the maintenance man for them you see, well he died very early and - and my husband was
 at Lockets learning engraving. Well, he was .....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 This was when you were first }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3280094 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 
No, this was while we were courting. And then - his mother was wanting some reliance on the children so he gave up that and took his dad's job on because he
'd always helped his dad in the place you see - in the workshop. So he went into maintenance - joinering and wheel weighting and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 I thought it was engineering?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 No, Browns the - Browns the butchers were the - the carts and - the 
- the blocks that they chopped the meat on and all that kind of thing he - he did all that kind of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Did you have to save up to get }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3280094 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090  in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 I'll say. Oh, did we. Definite. Well, put a bob or two here and when you could - when
 I could manage to save. I didn't manage to save much on my side I don't think but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 How long were you engaged?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Oh let me see - perhaps two years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Did your parents help you set up your home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 No. No. Went and got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3280094 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090  very quietly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 You didn't have a big wedding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 No, I didn't - I just slid off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Did you have presents and guests though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 No. No, just had witnesses, that was all. Yes, it was a very quiet wedding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Did you have a honeymoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 No. Not in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Where did you live after you were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3280094 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Lived in Seedley. Yes. And then -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Do you remember the street by any chance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 I'm just trying to think of it. It was off Langworthy Road I know that. I'll try thinking as I go along.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 How many years did you live there in that first house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Three months. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3352693\charrsid9666090 
'Cos we were - it belonged to a Buckley and Brennan's I think was the name of the mill and they used to have some very heavy machinery running 'and it used to shake the house to pi
eces so - we couldn't stand it any longer so we - friend of ours got us a house - spoke of a house - told us about a house in Wardley. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 
Just outside of Swinton there. And - we took that house on the main Manchester Road and were there three - three and a half years about.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 And then you came back to Salford?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 And then I came back to one of our own houses in Broughton.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 How old was your husband when you were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3280094 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 How old was he? Same age as me - within - nine months younger than me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 That was how old?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 He'd be nearly twenty-seven wouldn't he.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Did he always stay with Browns as a wheelwright?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 He stayed with them until - the - I told you about -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 He emigrated didn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Yes, he emigrated and there was a friend 
of the Browns who got into trouble - he got a brother abroad who used to send him a - a decent cheque now and again and he was - killed in an accident this brother abroad so of course naturally it did this fellow - a bad turn because he hadn't got the mon
ey and Browns felt sorry for him I suppose and they thought Mr Stones was a younger man than him so of course that finished that you see. He lost his job. And then he went abroad. He went abroad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 To Australia?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Yes. We were all - we were all - I was going too but - they'd mined the seas you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 This was when the first world war was on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Yes. Oh yes, first world war. He went on Christmas Eve 1913.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 You didn't work while you were first }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3280094 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090  though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 No. No. It was hard to get jobs then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Did your husband like his job as a wheelwright?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 
Very well, very much - yes, he liked it very much. He made that desk, you see that round desk there, yes, and that one hanging on the wall in the scullery in the kitchen rather. Yes, he made those.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Did he intend to do the same work when he got to Australia do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 
Oh, I suppose he would do - yes. But I - 'course with the war breaking out they were looking for recruits and - he was working in an engineers place I think, fro
m all accounts and then a - a ship put into - to - deck with an engineer dead abroad and so of course they persuaded him at the firm - they said it was a good opportunity to take that on so of course he went on there. Well, then they were taking supplies 
- to the scene of the - war, I suppose, to and fro with the British India Steam Engine - British India Steam Navigations Company. Well, then as time went on his letters ceased and we never heard no more about him. Never heard.....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 'Til you were left a widow?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Yes, well - left a grass widow. I don't know whether I'm a widow yet love.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Well, you were in the position of a widow - because you had a hard time didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 I know - yes, I had a very difficult time but ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Is it something you feel you can talk about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Oh, it doesn't worry me now, love.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 You had one child - a boy - didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 That's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 What year was he born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 19 - wait a minute - no, he's fifty-six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 It's a nineteen thirteen then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 That's it - that's right. June - June the twenty-fourth 1913.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Was he born at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 He was born at home love. He was born at my mothers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Did you know what to expect in those days when your baby was born or hadn't anybody told you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 No, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 How did you get on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 To tell you the real truth I always thought babies came through the naval. Yes. Right up 'til then - I was so -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Up until the baby was born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Did you have medical help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Had the midwife - for a month - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 How long were you kept in bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Well, I had a nervous breakdown you see after my husband went, you see, and I wasn't altogether }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3352693\charrsid9666090 compos}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3352693\charrsid9666090 mentis}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 
 when he was born, if you can understand.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 It would be a great shock though - not knowing where babies came from wouldn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Well, I - I didn't know. I thought that that was what your little hole in your tummy was for.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Did you have a nurse at all to help you - how long did she stay with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 No, I just had midwife - she was a nurse of course. She stayed a month.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 How long were you kept in bed in those days - do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 I think I was kept in bed a fortnight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 What did the midwife do for the baby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Oh, she washed it and dressed it and looked after me as well - 'cos I wasn't able to do much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Were you able to feed the baby yourself?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Oh yes, yes, I fed the baby and I could have fed two or three babies.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 You liked feeding it yourself did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Well, I - yes, I felt that it was more sustai
ning to a baby then - well, I - I don't think I ever thought of a bottle - didn't bother with bottles and wanting to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 But not everyone could breast feed a baby could they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Well, no, I don't think as many as they - they pretend they can't today. 
A lot of them today could I think only they - they want their figures back again, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 But you didn't mind that or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 No. I fed - fed him all the time until he was nine months old. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Suppose you had trouble with the baby who did you ask for advice - could you go to your mother then - now you were at home did she change?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Oh yes, she - she was very fond of the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3352693\charrsid9666090 kiddy}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090  and - and if he wasn't well she'd be I think I told you about him having - whooping cough and I'd chased off to the doctors. Yes. And I gave him some tartremetic.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 What was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 That - he - he had this cough -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Was this when he was quite young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Yes, he'd be about - perhaps nine months old - something like that. And this cough was worrying hi
m so - mother and I we said well we'd better got the doctor to him. Well, I rushed out to find the doctor. He wasn't in. And in the meantime his surgery - they'd gone to live at - privately up at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3352693\charrsid9666090 Marsal}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 . I - I fled up to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3352693\charrsid9666090 Marsal}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 
 and - he was out at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3352693\charrsid9666090 the time}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 
 or something of the kind and so I - I come back and I said I can't find a doctor anywhere mum. So, I had a book that a cousin of mine who was a teacher and - she'd given to me. It was - all about the care of children and I just happened to look for this 
and I saw whooping caught and it went on to tell me about tartremetic powders and - I remember it quite well, and - I went to the chemist and asked for this }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13982993\charrsid9666090 tartremetic}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090  and he asked me what it was for and all about it and I told him - told him I'd been look
ing for the doctor and I couldn't find him and all that kind of thing. And - he said well now be very careful how old was the baby - and I told him and he said, well, - I'd only give him half this powder. So I went home and of course - I don't ever rememb
er feeling all up about it - wondering if it was wrong or right or anything - I just gave it to the child - a half of this powder. And all of a sudden he vomited up and - he was as right as rain ten minutes afterwards. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 What were the rules about fe
eding in those days when your baby was little - did you feed him if he woke in the night or did you stick to special times?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Well, he used to have a feed at six o'clock in the evening - half past five to six. He went to bed half past five to six. And 
then he'd wake up at two in the morning and I'd give him a feed. Yes. And then - I'd hear no more about him then until ten o'clock the next morning. And then I'd try to do some shop - the shopping to get the dinner - 'cos I'd a dinner to get ready for qua
r
ter past twelve and many time I just had to wrap him up in a shawl - put him in his pram - dash off to the butchers and get the meat and what was necessary for the dinner and then come back and - get the meat on or whatever it was we were having and then 
I'd give him his bath. Dress him up - put him out in his pram on the front garden - there was a little garden at the front and I'd hear no more about him then until about half past two in the afternoon. He was a really good baby.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 You didn't have any trouble with him at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 No, no, not at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 You weaned him at nine months you said?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Did you put him straight onto solid food then or did you do it gradually?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 No, I think it - my mother said pobbies - bread and milk. Yes, an
d I'm having pobbies in the morning now. Yes, so he started on bread and milk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Did he mind - did he take to solid food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 As far as I knew he did - I don't remember him being funny about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 In those days if a baby cried do you think it did him any harm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 No, they used to say it strengthened the lungs to cry a bit - yes it strengthened the lungs to cry a bit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Did you ever punish him when he was naughty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 No, I don't remember giving him a good hiding - only once. I gave him a goo
d smacking when - later on in life - when I'd - I was working at the Ministry of Labour and it was pay out day - we'd had a very heavy day and - we were only supposed to pay out once a day but due to some - something not turning up or somebody not turning
 
up I'd paid out three times that day and - I was very - mentally tired when I got home. Hubert hadn't been so very good I suppose and the landlady said that you know, started on about our boy and I went upstairs and he was in bed and I beat him. And that'
s the only time I ever remember giving ..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Was your husband at home when he was born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Yes, when he was born, only six months after.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Did he help you during those six months - bathing him and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 But the rest of the time you'd got to bring him up on your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 
I'd got to struggle along - yes. But the point that used to annoy me was - I was working and - putting stamps on my card and all the rest of it but when the boy came to be poorly at all or he had a lit
tle accident and we were requiring a doctor a widow had to pay the doctors fee.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 This was before 1918 was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Yes. No, this was - after 1914 yes. And a man was insured with his wife and family for his subscription but I never could see the differ
ence between a widow being left with children to bring up to a man being left and having a wife to help him as well. And that annoyed me - used to annoy me and it used to stick in my craw.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Was this before 1918 though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Well, it - it affected whil
e the boy was from six to ten or twelve something like that but of course he was a fairly healthy boy as it happened. Apart from little accidents - he got a swing banged in his nose and it knocked his nose all up and blacked his eyes and that kind of thin
g
 but - that was a very sore point with me always - I couldn't see the difference between a widow bringing up a family and a man with the help of a wife bringing up a family and he should have free doctor treatment for the whole of them and one subscriptio
n and a widow trying to bring her family up on her subscription it only just encouraged - it only just covered her but not her child.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 When your baby was born you were at your mothers - how long did you stay there after that - you'd go to your own home 
would you with your husband?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Yes, three years I stayed with mother - yes. Then. And then it got so over - bearing I couldn't stick it no longer.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Your mother didn't soften any towards you as you got older?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 No, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Usually grandmothers do don't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 
They - some - well my dad was very soft with the child - he - he thought the world of the boy. I always said when my dad - when Hubert lost his granddad he lost a - a big friend. But .....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 So actually you did have some help in the beginning bringing the boy up did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Well, yes, help - but I had to work jolly hard in return for it. I had to do all the housework and ....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 As well as going out to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 I didn't go to work then love, three years at home, with my mother. At - at -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 After the baby was born you'd three years at home with your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 But your husband was then in Australia wasn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Was in Australia - that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 And you had to work darned hard for the help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Tha
t's right. It was a case of if I couldn't give something in return I wouldn't have got very much consideration I don't think. But still, that's neither here nor there - we got through it and then after three and a half years - a certain little altercation
 
happened at home and I said I couldn't stick it any longer. It - as a matter of fact it was I wanted to take the boy down to Lucy's to see the Christmas decorations you see and it was Friday and mother said well, who's going to do the work while you're aw
a
y? So I said oh well, it'll get done, I'll do it tomorrow or something and of course she was very annoyed and when I came back - of course there was an uproar started and - and I'm afraid it wasn't very pleasant so I made up my mind I'd get a job of some 
kind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 When you had your own home did you change your attitude to bringing up children from what your mother had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Oh, def -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Did you bring up your boy in a totally different way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Oh definitely. Oh yes. But you see we were mostly in digs 
you see - the child and I. I had - go into to digs to have someone to look after him while I was working you see. Well, it - it was a matter of -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Were you lucky in this - in the people who looked after him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Fairly. Yes, fairly lucky I must say. 
But the last one was an old lady that - she wasn't very old - lived in one of the streets just below there and - I knew her through her mother being my sisters landlady you see and she was a - a spinster and her - mother had died and - so my sister took m
e
 up to have a look - have a chat with her and that so she said - oh yes, she'd be very pleased to have us because it would be company for her. Well, we stayed with her eight years you see, and during that period - she was very fond of the child - and she 
looked after him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 She taught him table manners and all that sort of thing did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 No, no, I taught - I taught him all that - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Were you strict with him like your mother was with you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 No. No, no, no. No. God forbid that - and - any
 - any child should be brought under that strict regime that - that's terrible. You know ....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Did you find a big difference in your standard of living suddenly being left a widow - and eating patterns and everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Oh I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 You were used to big hams at home weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 
That's right. We used to going in the cellar and slicing off lumps as we wanted it you see, but when we got to buying half pounds at a time and - and that it seemed - oh I don't know what it was - it - it seemed meager somehow. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Providing clothes and shoes and things like that would be difficult?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Yes. Well, I was always pretty light on shoes - clothes - I never was very heavy on clothes - never have been.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 What about the child though - you'd have a job with the child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 
Oh yes. Well, dad - my dad - he used to take him down to the Don's Tailors in Market Street and - he - oh and he'd buy him a little rig out - he was very good. And my sister - she bought him his first little knitted suit - you kno
w. We got through all right for ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Would they help you with this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Oh yes. They were very helpful like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 How did you cope though with a full time job and then having to come home with a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 Don't ask me, love. When I look back 
and I think as I'd been - totting up figures and all of a sudden I've thought oh I wonder what's happening to that lad - is he all right. And then I'd start crying. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3352693\charrsid9666090 
And - I remember this - the supervisor at O'Connell's, she came to me and she'd say, now, now, now, is there anything I can do for you. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 
And I - she was very nice indeed and I got around but of course that was in the very early years - later on I - I think I must have get hardened or something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 There wasn't much help for widows in those days was there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 There was no help at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641509 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 You had to do it entirely on your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1340632 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10756693\charrsid9666090 
Every - everything was done on your own. You - there was no family helps and things like that when Hubert was a baby. So you'd just have to figure it out the best way you could.
\par }}